              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The block receives a timestamp matching that of the first buffer to which all settings have been applied. The timestamp is synchronized to the device clock, and thus must be converted to the system clock before comparison with the timestamps of buffers delivered via an "
